text: Thryptomene strongylophylla is a shrub species in the family Myrtaceae that is endemic to Western Australia. The straggly shrub typically grows to a height of . It blooms between May and November producing pink-purple flowers. It is found on sand plains and sand dunes in the Wheatbelt, Mid West and Gascoyne regions of Western Australia between Shark Bay and Carnamah where it grows in sandy soils. ==References== strongylophylla Category:Endemic flora of Western Australia Category:Rosids of Western Australia Category:Taxa named by George Bentham Category:Plants described in 1867
